Implementation Checklist for Error-Free Lead Generation Planning
Before launching your lead generation initiative, work through this implementation checklist to ensure you've addressed each potential error. First, document your ideal customer profile with specific criteria for company size, industry, geography, job titles, and pain points. Second, define what constitutes a marketing qualified lead and establish service level agreements between marketing and sales teams. Third, implement lead scoring based on both fit and engagement criteria, ensuring balanced attention to quality alongside volume. Fourth, activate integrations between your marketing technology and CRM systems, establishing data governance standards and automated lead routing rules. Fifth, establish monthly optimization rhythms with systematic review of key metrics and testing of incremental improvements.

Beyond the initial setup, commit to quarterly strategy reviews. Assess whether your ICP remains accurate based on actual customer data. Review whether MQL definitions still align with sales' experience. Evaluate whether your lead scoring model predicts conversion accurately. Analyze whether your technology stack continues serving your needs or if upgrades or additions would improve efficiency.

